sources.title: In Old Cheyenne (1941) ROY ROGERS
sources.description:
Stars: Roy Rogers, George 'Gabby' Hayes, Joan Woodbury
Director: Joseph Kane

 Roy is a newspaper reporter. He goes to Cheyenne to cover the activities of supposed bad guy Arapahoe Brown. Roy, of course, discovers who the real bad guy is.

metadata.Plot: Reporter Steve Blane arrives in Cheyenne looking for the famous outlaw Arapahoe Brown. But when Arapahoe saves his life, he learns that Sam Drummond is the real outlaw and his gang are impersonating Arapahoe and his men. With the hoax now exposed, Drummond and his men chase Blane to a ranch where he and a few others find themselves outnumbered and once again in need of Arapahoe's help.
metadata.Actors: Roy Rogers, George 'Gabby' Hayes, Joan Woodbury
